Laikipia Governor Joshua Irungu yesterday condemned an incident where he was booed in Nanyuki town on Monday during President Uhuru Kenyatta&rsquo;s visit.In a press statement sent to media houses, he accused some governor hopefuls, whom he did not name, of being behind it. During the function at Central Park, the public booed the governor and refused to be addressed by him.&ldquo;The office of the governor condemns in the strongest words possible the action of a section of aspirants who hired some youths to boo down elected leaders, specifically the governor,&rdquo; the statement read.Irungu alleged the youths were paid to humiliate county leaders in Uhuru&rsquo;s presence.He warned against recurrence, adding they might have satisfied their ego but achieved nothing.